theorem Topology.closure_interior_iter_six_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
      (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (A : Set X))))))))))) =
      closure (interior A) := by
  -- First, collapse the five-fold iteration that appears inside.
  have h₁ :
      closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior
        (closure (interior (closure (interior (A : Set X))))))))) ) =
        closure (interior A) :=
    Topology.closure_interior_iter_five_eq (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Rewriting with `h₁` turns the left side into
  -- `closure (interior (closure (interior A)))`, which can be
  -- simplified using the idempotence lemma.
  simpa [h₁,
        Topology.closure_interior_closure_interior_eq (X := X) (A := A)]

theorem Topology.interior_inter_closure_compl_eq_empty {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (A : Set X) ∩ closure (Aᶜ : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  -- Apply the previously proved lemma to the complement of `A`.
  simpa [Set.compl_compl, Set.inter_comm]
    using
      (Topology.interior_compl_inter_closure_eq_empty
        (X := X) (A := Aᶜ))

theorem Topology.interior_eq_compl_closure_compl {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    (A : Set X) :
    interior (A : Set X) = (closure ((A : Set X)ᶜ))ᶜ := by
  simpa [compl_compl] using (interior_compl (s := (Aᶜ : Set X)))
